ECPM - Equal-Cost Multi-Path
-------
Transit Gateway is a centralized hub connecting multiple VPCs and on-prem networks. ECMP distributes traffic across multiple equal-cost VPN tunnels simultaneously for higher throughput — each tunnel gives 1.25 Gbps so 4 tunnels give 5 Gbps total. ECMP requires BGP dynamic routing and must be enabled on Transit Gateway

No! VPN is not used for single VPC — it's used to connect outside networks to AWS.
-------------------
VPN use cases:
------------------
VPN is used to connect:

On-premise office → AWS VPC ✅
Your laptop (remote work) → AWS VPC ✅
Another cloud (Azure/GCP) → AWS VPC ✅
Data center → AWS VPC ✅

NOT used:
Within single VPC ❌
Between subnets in same VPC ❌

When you need VPN:

+-----------------------------+------------------------------+
| Scenario                    | Solution                     |
+-----------------------------+------------------------------+
| Office → AWS                | Site-to-Site VPN             |
| Remote developer → AWS      | Client VPN                   |
| Multiple VPCs               | Transit Gateway (not VPN)    |
| On-prem → multiple VPCs     | TGW + VPN                    |
+-----------------------------+------------------------------+

ECMP:

Without ECMP:
  VPN Tunnel 1 → active (1.25 Gbps)
  VPN Tunnel 2 → standby ❌
  Only one tunnel used ❌

With ECMP:
  VPN Tunnel 1 → active (1.25 Gbps) ✅
  VPN Tunnel 2 → active (1.25 Gbps) ✅
  VPN Tunnel 3 → active (1.25 Gbps) ✅
  VPN Tunnel 4 → active (1.25 Gbps) ✅
  Total = 5 Gbps ✅
  All tunnels used simultaneously ✅
-----------------------------------------------
if we enable on transit g/w how many vpn will active?

All VPN tunnels will be active simultaneously!

Each VPN connection has 2 tunnels:

VPN Connection 1:
  Tunnel 1 → active ✅
  Tunnel 2 → active ✅

VPN Connection 2:
  Tunnel 3 → active ✅
  Tunnel 4 → active ✅

VPN Connection 3:
  Tunnel 5 → active ✅
  Tunnel 6 → active ✅

Without ECMP:

VPN Connection 1:
  Tunnel 1 → active ✅
  Tunnel 2 → standby ❌   ← wasted

VPN Connection 2:
  Tunnel 3 → active ✅
  Tunnel 4 → standby ❌   ← wasted

Only 2 tunnels used out of 4 ❌

----------------------------------------------
There is no fixed limit — you can attach as many VPN connections as you need!

AWS TGW VPN limits:

Per Transit Gateway:
  Max VPN connections: 5000 ✅
  Each VPN has 2 tunnels
  5000 VPNs × 2 tunnels = 10,000 tunnels

But practical limit:
  TGW max bandwidth: 50 Gbps
  Each tunnel: 1.25 Gbps
  50 Gbps ÷ 1.25 = 40 tunnels max useful
  = 20 VPN connections practical limit
